2. Click on the 'User' button (Managing Users)<br>
3. Click on the 'User Levels' button<br>
4. Click on the 'Add New Level' button<br>
5. Enter a level number (I started with 1 and counted up)<br>
6. Enter a Title of your choice (Space Cadet, or whatever)<br>
7. Assign powers given to that Level/Title (Admin, Mod, Standard) I<br>
picked 'standard' until user reaches high levels (ie, lots of posts)<br>
8.Choose if promoted automatically (and if auto, then how many posts<br>
required to be promoted to that Level/Title). <br>
9. When ready click on the 'Add New Level' button. <br>
10. Wash, Rinse and Repeat for as many levels as you desire! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fusion Starship Captain</span><br>  Posts: 307<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/8/02 6:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fas.org/nuke/hew/Usa/Tests/Rwmohawk2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: about those titles... </span><hr size=1> I wanted the &quot;NERVA Spaceplane Pilot&quot; Title!<br>
